# Implementation Plan - Optimize Dev Startup

The Paperclip dev runner is getting stuck during the build phase of the `@paperclipai/plugin-sdk` package. On Windows, `tsc` and `pnpm` workspace operations can be significantly slower or prone to locking issues. Since I have already successfully built the entire workspace manually, this build step in the dev runner is currently redundant and acting as a bottleneck.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Optimize Dev Runner
I will temporarily bypass the mandatory build step for the plugin SDK in the dev runner to allow the server to start immediately using the existing build artifacts.

#### [MODIFY] [dev-runner.mjs](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/scripts/dev-runner.mjs)
- Comment out the `await buildPluginSdk();` call in `startServerChild()`.

### 2. Cleanup & Restart
1. Terminate all processes.
2. Run `run.bat`.

